Rating: 3
Excellent introduction for new foods for little ones. My 6 year old and 2 year old were both fine with it. Next time I would omit the chopped onion and use onion powder. The 6 year old did not like the chopped onion. Tasty for adults too! Moist and good flavor.

Rating: 4
Not only was this kid-friendly, it was adult-friendly as well. The problem with most turkey burgers is that they tend to dry out when you cook them. But in this recipe the fresh bread crumbs and oil gave the burgers nice texture and helped keep the turkey moist. My two year old ate an entire burger on his own. That's how good they are! I grilled the burgers and left out the onions. I think grilling may also have helped keep the burgers moist.

Rating: 3
This is one of the best ground turkey recipes I have found. I substituted provolone cheese for the cheddar and added bacon to the sandwiches, because that's what I had on hand and they turned out to be quite good. The burgers themselves were a little dry, but tasty.